questions: 6. Consider a hash table of size seven, with starting index zero, and a hash function (3x + 4)mod7. \xa0\xa0\xa0\xa00    1   2   3   4   5   6

\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa00    1   2   3   4   5   6

\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa00    1   2   3   4   5   6
The value of function (3x + 4)mod 7 for 8 is 0, but 0 is already occupied, let us put the value(8) at next available space(1)

\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa00    1   2   3   4   5   6
